Two blasts caused by home-made bombs rocked the remote town of Turbat some 500 kilometres 310 miles west of the provincial capital Quetta late Saturday Baluchistan home secretary Humayun Khan told AFP
During the 1970s Baluchistan was the scene of a major uprising which was brutally put down by the government
Four people were injured and a powerline and a government office damaged in three separate bomb blasts in southwestern Pakistans restive Baluchistan province officials said Sunday
A parliamentary committee has been set up to examine the grievances of the tribesmen in Baluchistan which was roiled by insurgency in the 1970s and make recommendations to the government
